data.content:
Two files created:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Renders a `<ul>` with each item's template plus Move Up/Down buttons. Buttons are disabled at list boundaries. Uses `@key` for efficient diffing.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Code-behind with:
- `Items` (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) — copied to a private `_items` list in `OnParametersSet` (never mutates the parent's list)
- `ItemTemplate` (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) — templated rendering
- `OnOrderChanged` (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) — fires after each swap with a read-only snapshot

Usage matches your example — just note the callback receives `IReadOnlyList<TItem>`:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskItem> tasks = new() { ... };

    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskItem> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
